BLOCKING — Must fix before distribution
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[FIXED June 18, 2026] DB Indexes — idx_stats_game_id, idx_stats_player_id,
  idx_stats_team_id, idx_stats_team_game, idx_games_season, and
  idx_games_season_sim added to database.ts via CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS.

[FIXED June 18, 2026] Migration Versioning — schema_version tracked in
  settings; numbered migration runner upgrades existing saves on launch.

[FIXED June 18, 2026] Multiple Save Files — DB path no longer hardcoded;
  save picker at launch swaps active DB file before database module loads.

[FIXED June 18, 2026] Background Simulation — simulateGame runs in a worker
  thread. UI stays responsive during full-season sim.

[FIXED June 18, 2026] Full IP Cleanup — all real NFL data removed:
  Madden ratings CSV, OTC contracts, career stats CSVs, historical records
  CSVs. Replaced with fictional player generator (53-man rosters + 176 FAs).
  Championship renamed Super Bowl → Gridiron Cup. All NFL trademark
  references removed from UI. App renamed to Gridiron Dynasty.

Code Signing + Auto-Update — Electron apps without code signing trigger OS
  security warnings (macOS Gatekeeper, Windows SmartScreen). Needs
  electron-builder code signing and electron-updater before public distribution.

Windows Build Verification — better-sqlite3 is a native module that must be
  built per platform. Needs a GitHub Actions CI workflow that builds and
  tests on Windows before Steam submission.

IMPORTANT — Fix before growing the codebase further
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[FIXED June 18, 2026] Automated Tests — comprehensive Vitest suite covering
  simulation helpers, game sim logic, season progression, trade value,
  contract acceptance, milestones, CPU GM logic, and team stats.

CSV Import System — users need a way to import custom rosters, historical
  records benchmarks, and player data. Required to re-enable the Records
  benchmarks feature now that built-in NFL data is removed.

Reduce `any` in IPC Handlers — Most handler callbacks use `any` extensively.
  Needs typed request/response interfaces as the feature set grows.

FUTURE DEPTH — Required to compete with OOTP-tier games
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Sim Speed Control — Fast / slow / pause controls while simulation runs in
  background. Standard expectation in the genre.

Multi-Season Batch Simulation — "Sim 5 seasons" with a progress bar. Requires
  background simulation to be implemented first.

Realistic Schedule Generation — Current schedule is random matchups. Needs
  division-based scheduling (home/away splits, divisional games weighted).

Per-Team Franchise History — Records, retired numbers, dynasty timeline per
  team. Partial today (champions only).

Player Morale / Personality — Affects re-sign decisions, locker room culture,
  performance variance. A core OOTP mechanic.

In-Game Narrative / Play-by-Play — Text play-by-play during simulation.
  Stats-only output today limits immersion significantly.

Franchise Tag + Tender System — Standard franchise mechanic missing today.

League Expansion / Relocation — Add teams, move teams, custom identities.
